1
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:08,080
Want it?

2
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:24,440
Boss might not want it, but I do.

3
00:04:30,240 --> 00:04:31,520
Hey.

4
00:05:12,960 --> 00:05:15,880
If anyone pulls a gun,
your boss is done for.

5
00:05:22,080 --> 00:05:23,320
Hey, Ya.

6
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,320
Warn your boss's kid.

7
00:05:26,920 --> 00:05:29,280
He just got back from abroad.
He probably doesn't know

8
00:05:29,360 --> 00:05:32,240
that doing business on someone else's turf

9
00:05:32,320 --> 00:05:33,720
means paying protection.

10
00:05:49,520 --> 00:05:51,520
Your tiny little turf?

11
00:05:52,240 --> 00:05:56,160
You swear you've never crossed
into my father's territory?

12
00:06:03,120 --> 00:06:04,600
If we were the ones collecting money,

13
00:06:06,000 --> 00:06:08,160
you wouldn't be able
to pay it off in your whole life.

14
00:06:08,240 --> 00:06:10,040
Don't give me that crap.

15
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:13,360
You're selling illegal goods on our turf.

16
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:15,640
This is my boss's territory.

17
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:18,200
If you don't pay, you're not leaving.

18
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,720
Boss, just give it to them.

19
00:06:26,800 --> 00:06:28,440
Their boss probably ordered it.

20
00:06:47,120 --> 00:06:49,760
I'd rather throw it away
than give it to you.

21
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:53,640
You've got a big mouth!

22
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:55,120
- Hey!
- Stop!

23
00:06:55,200 --> 00:06:56,720
Stop.

24
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:02,000
Hey!

25
00:07:23,040 --> 00:07:23,880
Hey!

26
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:33,200
What?!

27
00:08:24,520 --> 00:08:25,680
Let go!

28
00:09:18,160 --> 00:09:20,360
Bullets are too expensive for you.

29
00:10:00,840 --> 00:10:02,520
Here.

30
00:10:04,120 --> 00:10:06,520
Whoa. You didn't even try that hard.

31
00:10:07,640 --> 00:10:09,400
I'm already broke from the ticket.

32
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:12,080
Or don't you want it?

33
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:21,120
Then I'll give it
to the lead actress instead.

34
00:10:22,880 --> 00:10:24,560
You're not giving it to anyone else.

35
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,160
They smell so nice.

36
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:49,520
Come on, let's take photos.

37
00:11:22,320 --> 00:11:23,680
Raka, did you know?

38
00:11:23,760 --> 00:11:27,960
At first, they wanted me to audition
for Mint, the third lead,

39
00:11:28,040 --> 00:11:31,440
but I didn't get it
because I didn't have money for surgery.

40
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:39,600
You're already so pretty.
People keep asking for your LINE.

41
00:11:39,680 --> 00:11:40,960
I'm already jealous.

42
00:11:42,400 --> 00:11:45,760
They didn't choose you
because they don't have good taste.

43
00:11:46,880 --> 00:11:48,320
But it's necessary, Raka.

44
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:50,960
All actors do it.

45
00:11:51,040 --> 00:11:53,400
That role needed someone
who glows, like a rich girl.

46
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,280
Fah, the one who got it,

47
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,320
gets facial treatments all the time.

48
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:59,120
How am I supposed to compete?

49
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:02,720
What about the money
you asked your dad for the clinic?

50
00:12:09,120 --> 00:12:12,840
You know my dad
doesn't support me being an actress.

51
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:17,360
He wants me to work a stable office job.

52
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:20,800
Every time we talk about it, I feel bad.

53
00:12:29,240 --> 00:12:30,560
Poor me, right?

54
00:12:33,560 --> 00:12:37,640
Whatever. Let's drop it.
Talking won't change anything.

55
00:12:38,200 --> 00:12:39,160
Let's go home.

56
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,440
Let's go.

57
00:12:52,640 --> 00:12:56,040
Please. In just a few more months,
I'll graduate and start working.

58
00:12:56,120 --> 00:12:57,800
I'll have a salary.

59
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:59,400
I'll pay for the course in installments.

60
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:06,320
I knew it. That's why
you brought me a gift.

61
00:13:07,480 --> 00:13:10,760
You want to pay in installments
for your girlfriend's facial treatments?

62
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:13,240
Didn't you say you like natural beauty?

63
00:13:13,320 --> 00:13:15,400
I do like her the way she is.

64
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:19,000
But May said the competition
in the industry is intense.

65
00:13:19,080 --> 00:13:21,560
If she doesn't do anything,
it's hard to compete.

66
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:24,760
There are people who don't do anything.

67
00:13:26,520 --> 00:13:28,760
But not many.

68
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:31,640
That's exactly why I opened this clinic.

69
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,440
Hey, let me ask you something.

70
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:37,720
If you love her this much,

71
00:13:37,800 --> 00:13:40,080
why not propose before your internship?

72
00:13:40,160 --> 00:13:43,640
If it weren't for her wanting
to become a professional actress first,

73
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,280
I would've proposed already.

74
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:52,320
I was just teasing.

75
00:13:52,400 --> 00:13:54,600
A man should try
holding on to his single life.

76
00:13:55,160 --> 00:13:56,920
Got it?

77
00:13:58,960 --> 00:14:00,440
Is that a yes?

78
00:14:02,040 --> 00:14:03,600
Thank you.

79
00:14:07,560 --> 00:14:09,760
Where's the doctor?

80
00:14:12,920 --> 00:14:15,280
Sir, this is a beauty clinic.

81
00:14:15,880 --> 00:14:16,920
Where's the doctor?

82
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:21,960
Doctor! Where are you?

83
00:14:22,640 --> 00:14:24,080
Hey? What happened?

84
00:14:36,080 --> 00:14:37,720
Treat my father.

85
00:14:40,040 --> 00:14:42,400
You know who my father is, right?

86
00:14:45,120 --> 00:14:47,280
Yes, but…

87
00:14:47,360 --> 00:14:50,280
If you don't want those guys outside
coming in here shooting,

88
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,680
keep quiet.

89
00:14:55,280 --> 00:14:56,800
Ms. Bee,

90
00:14:56,880 --> 00:14:58,160
take the customers out first.

91
00:14:58,240 --> 00:14:59,200
Yes, right away.

92
00:14:59,280 --> 00:15:00,880
Alright.

93
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:06,600
Everyone, please head outside first.
This way, please.

94
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,640
Sir.

95
00:15:09,720 --> 00:15:12,200
You're going to get us into trouble.

96
00:15:14,560 --> 00:15:17,360
How about this? I'll call an ambulance.

97
00:15:17,440 --> 00:15:19,960
You know who runs this area, right?

98
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:25,040
Uh…

99
00:15:34,000 --> 00:15:36,000
Please, help me.

100
00:15:36,600 --> 00:15:39,200
I'll give you that course
for your girlfriend for free,

101
00:15:39,280 --> 00:15:40,520
full-body, everything.

102
00:15:41,640 --> 00:15:44,720
Are you crazy? I'm just an intern.

103
00:15:46,320 --> 00:15:47,360
Sir,

104
00:15:48,640 --> 00:15:51,680
he is a surgical doctor.
He's more capable than me.

105
00:15:52,840 --> 00:15:56,080
He looks way too young.
Are you trying to fool me?

106
00:15:58,000 --> 00:16:00,040
Are you two

107
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:02,640
looking for an excuse
not to treat my boss?

108
00:16:07,360 --> 00:16:09,000
So you're not helping?

109
00:16:09,720 --> 00:16:12,120
That's why you brought
this baby-faced kid to trick me?

110
00:16:22,600 --> 00:16:24,120
Do you want him treated or not?

111
00:17:16,920 --> 00:17:18,520
I think there's internal bleeding.

112
00:17:19,319 --> 00:17:22,160
A lot of it. He should go to a hospital.

113
00:17:29,200 --> 00:17:30,680
Are you deaf?

114
00:17:35,920 --> 00:17:38,360
I said, treat my father.

115
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:14,560
If you mess this up
and my boss doesn't survive,

116
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,280
you won't either.

117
00:18:26,200 --> 00:18:30,000
<i>Today, I will teach you</i>
<i>how to perform surgery on a cadaver.</i>

118
00:18:30,080 --> 00:18:34,000
The main incision we'll be focusing on
today is the low midline,

119
00:18:34,080 --> 00:18:36,240
making a straight incision
along the lower abdomen.

120
00:18:36,320 --> 00:18:37,600
Watch carefully.

121
00:18:38,840 --> 00:18:40,600
Retract the incision properly.

122
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:44,080
Peeraka, go ahead
and make the incision for me.

123
00:18:44,160 --> 00:18:46,320
Follow the same line I showed you earlier.

124
00:18:46,400 --> 00:18:49,080
Go on, give it a try.

125
00:19:02,680 --> 00:19:05,640
Can you all see
where the incision should be?

126
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:09,880
Yes, I can. The white line
is about one centimeter from my finger.

127
00:19:10,760 --> 00:19:12,400
Very good.

128
00:19:14,000 --> 00:19:15,120
How can he see that?

129
00:19:15,200 --> 00:19:16,560
I still can't see anything.

130
00:19:58,520 --> 00:20:02,640
Bring the car to the back.
We'll be out in five minutes.

131
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:15,760
If anything happens to my father,

132
00:20:22,840 --> 00:20:24,880
start preparing your own funeral.

133
00:20:47,840 --> 00:20:50,320
Don't scream, if you don't
want to end up in the ER.

134
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:55,240
Let's go.

135
00:22:10,320 --> 00:22:14,160
What's the matter? Why drag me here?

136
00:22:15,680 --> 00:22:19,240
Why did you drag him here like that?
That's bad behavior.

137
00:22:19,320 --> 00:22:21,600
Didn't I tell you?

138
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,240
- But Boss--
- Hey.

139
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,760
Sorry, Boss.

140
00:22:32,640 --> 00:22:33,800
And you too.

141
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:36,440
That day, he was about
to perform surgery on me,

142
00:22:36,520 --> 00:22:38,160
and you were about to slap him.

143
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:41,680
Sorry, Doctor.

144
00:22:44,040 --> 00:22:45,520
And you too, Wayu.

145
00:22:57,360 --> 00:22:58,680
Sorry.

146
00:23:11,960 --> 00:23:13,080
It's fine.

147
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,880
You don't have to do this.

148
00:23:19,200 --> 00:23:21,160
We're not good people.

149
00:23:21,240 --> 00:23:24,600
But we have one rule.

150
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:30,280
If someone helps us, we repay them.

151
00:23:38,240 --> 00:23:42,720
I've already checked the CCTV footage
from the day you operated on me.

152
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:50,480
Someone like me, I check everything.

153
00:23:52,800 --> 00:23:56,840
What you did that day,
it wasn't out of fear for these guys.

154
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:04,160
You genuinely wanted to help me.

155
00:24:07,280 --> 00:24:10,600
I'm glad I met a doctor like you.

156
00:24:11,680 --> 00:24:15,880
A doctor who treats patients
without caring who they are

157
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,520
or what they've done.

158
00:24:22,360 --> 00:24:24,120
I'm impressed.

159
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:27,320
Even my personal doctor said

160
00:24:28,280 --> 00:24:31,600
that if it weren't for you that day,

161
00:24:31,680 --> 00:24:35,240
I wouldn't be sitting here
talking right now.

162
00:24:37,400 --> 00:24:38,760
So…

163
00:24:40,560 --> 00:24:41,520
Praya.

164
00:24:52,160 --> 00:24:53,920
Write any amount you want.

165
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:07,120
You said it yourself,
what I did was to help you.

166
00:25:08,400 --> 00:25:12,040
If it's help, there's no need
to settle it with money afterward.

167
00:25:16,520 --> 00:25:18,080
Too scared to take our money?

168
00:25:24,120 --> 00:25:26,720
You want us to pay you
in some other way instead?

169
00:25:27,480 --> 00:25:29,040
I guarantee no one will trace it back.

170
00:25:29,120 --> 00:25:31,520
No need, thanks.

171
00:25:36,960 --> 00:25:40,960
If you really want to help,
then don't do things like this again.

172
00:25:42,040 --> 00:25:43,160
I'll go now.

173
00:25:44,640 --> 00:25:46,360
Come work for me.

174
00:25:53,200 --> 00:25:56,680
You want money, don't you? I know.

175
00:25:58,280 --> 00:26:00,280
What you did for me,

176
00:26:01,120 --> 00:26:03,360
I'll repay you in another way.

177
00:26:05,760 --> 00:26:10,280
Someone like me, Chaichana,
I never take advantage of anyone.

178
00:26:11,320 --> 00:26:14,240
If you work for me, treating my people,

179
00:26:15,000 --> 00:26:17,240
I guarantee for the rest of your life,

180
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:21,000
whatever you want, you'll get it.

181
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:34,600
Thank you.

182
00:26:37,800 --> 00:26:40,400
But when I graduate,

183
00:26:41,600 --> 00:26:42,720
I want to treat patients.

184
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,920
What do you mean?

185
00:26:46,920 --> 00:26:48,600
Aren't we patients? Aren't we human?

186
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:51,040
Do you expect me to treat people
who point guns at others?

187
00:26:51,120 --> 00:26:52,720
Is that saving lives

188
00:26:53,440 --> 00:26:54,960
or destroying them?

189
00:26:55,040 --> 00:26:56,480
- Hey!
- Hey!

190
00:26:56,560 --> 00:27:00,480
Hey, come on. Don't be rude.

191
00:27:03,320 --> 00:27:04,680
That's a shame.

192
00:27:06,360 --> 00:27:10,120
I really wanted to be
on good terms with you.

193
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:16,880
But it's fine.

194
00:27:17,760 --> 00:27:21,600
I hope you're lucky enough
not to run into us again.

195
00:28:19,200 --> 00:28:23,520
Seriously, what kind of doctor
lives like this? So messy.

196
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:29,720
Do you smell something?

197
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:34,680
The most delicious fried chicken
in the world, Madam Vipa's special recipe.

198
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:41,240
Come on, have some.

199
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:44,240
It's still hot. Can you smell it?

200
00:28:44,320 --> 00:28:46,840
It's still hot. If it gets cold,
it won't taste as good.

201
00:28:46,920 --> 00:28:49,960
Mom, no. I can't eat.

202
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:56,760
Slow down.

203
00:28:56,840 --> 00:28:59,360
Finish it all.

204
00:28:59,440 --> 00:29:03,560
That's enough.
You're down to the bones now.

205
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,120
Here, wipe your mouth.

206
00:29:07,720 --> 00:29:10,000
You finished it so fast.

207
00:29:10,080 --> 00:29:11,000
Hey!

208
00:29:11,600 --> 00:29:14,320
- That's for Kul. Enough. You'll get fat.
- Mom.

209
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:19,560
Can I have one or two more pieces?

210
00:29:25,440 --> 00:29:27,520
Please, Mom. Please.

211
00:29:27,600 --> 00:29:29,920
- That's enough. You'll get fat.
- Please.

212
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:31,280
Please, Chef Vipa,
the most beautiful chef.

213
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:34,520
You make the best
fried chicken in the world.

214
00:29:34,600 --> 00:29:36,160
Just one piece.

215
00:29:36,240 --> 00:29:38,920
Alright, just one piece.

216
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,360
She's not here. She won't know.

217
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:44,200
You little thief.

218
00:29:45,520 --> 00:29:48,280
- Come on, just one piece.
- In front of me? This is mine.

219
00:29:48,360 --> 00:29:49,960
Mom already said yes. Look at her.

220
00:29:50,040 --> 00:29:52,760
Can I give your little brother
one piece? He's hungry.

221
00:29:52,840 --> 00:29:54,040
But I'm exhausted from work.

222
00:29:54,120 --> 00:29:55,920
- I'm tired too.
- Tired from what?

223
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:56,840
She worked hard.

224
00:29:56,920 --> 00:29:58,800
You're still in your home clothes.

225
00:29:58,880 --> 00:30:00,880
- Enough. You ate a whole plate.
- You play games all day.

226
00:30:00,960 --> 00:30:03,560
- That's enough.
- Yes, Mom. This is mine.

227
00:30:03,640 --> 00:30:05,640
- Come on!
- Hey!

228
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:10,080
- Don't. You'll spill it.
- I'll hit you!

229
00:30:18,480 --> 00:30:19,400
I'd like one piece, Dad.

230
00:30:19,480 --> 00:30:23,360
Hey, Raka! Mom.

231
00:30:23,960 --> 00:30:27,080
Mom, look at him. Even during
Dad's offering, he still steals.

232
00:30:28,200 --> 00:30:29,560
He's hungry.

233
00:30:29,640 --> 00:30:33,000
- That's disgusting.
- It's fine. It's fine.

234
00:30:33,080 --> 00:30:36,120
Dear, we have two children.

235
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:39,200
One is an outstanding journalist.

236
00:30:40,280 --> 00:30:43,720
And the other is an intern,
about to become a real doctor.

237
00:30:45,240 --> 00:30:47,560
If you were here, you'd be so proud.

238
00:30:49,480 --> 00:30:51,880
But there's one thing
he wouldn't be proud of.

239
00:30:53,840 --> 00:30:55,720
Kul's going to be single forever.

240
00:30:55,800 --> 00:30:58,440
She's been dating Win for so long,
and he still hasn't proposed.

241
00:30:59,560 --> 00:31:01,520
- Hey, Raka!
- I knew it.

242
00:31:02,520 --> 00:31:03,600
And what about you?

243
00:31:03,680 --> 00:31:06,240
Buying tickets to your girlfriend's play
over and over.

244
00:31:07,280 --> 00:31:10,160
If you're that rich,
give me the money instead.

245
00:31:14,880 --> 00:31:18,120
You don't have money? Fine.

246
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:19,320
Hey.

247
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:23,920
What's this?

248
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:26,960
Hey, that's my money.

249
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:28,680
- Give that back.
- Well, here we go.

250
00:31:28,760 --> 00:31:30,560
- She stole my money.
- Come on.

251
00:31:30,640 --> 00:31:32,200
Stop fighting.

252
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:35,240
Please. Your dad might hear you.

253
00:31:35,320 --> 00:31:37,640
I will if she gives it back.

254
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:38,960
No.

255
00:31:39,040 --> 00:31:40,840
- Hey! Give it back!
- No.

256
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:42,560
- Be careful.
- Mom!

257
00:31:42,640 --> 00:31:44,160
Don't hurt her.

258
00:31:44,240 --> 00:31:47,200
- Whoa.
- Mom!

259
00:31:56,560 --> 00:31:57,960
Why isn't Ya here yet?

260
00:31:58,040 --> 00:31:59,240
Right?

261
00:32:00,240 --> 00:32:01,560
Forget him.

262
00:32:03,440 --> 00:32:05,560
These days, he acts like he's my father.

263
00:32:06,840 --> 00:32:08,560
If he doesn't come, even better.

264
00:32:09,640 --> 00:32:10,680
Boss,

265
00:32:11,440 --> 00:32:12,560
they're here.

266
00:32:22,120 --> 00:32:23,000
Let's go.

267
00:32:24,160 --> 00:32:25,840
NONTHAPIMONCHAI

268
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:39,080
Get in the car.

269
00:32:43,760 --> 00:32:45,040
My motorbike.

270
00:32:46,720 --> 00:32:47,960
Whoa.

271
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:53,640
Start the engine now.

272
00:32:54,240 --> 00:32:55,360
It won't start.

273
00:32:58,560 --> 00:33:00,160
What the hell?!

274
00:33:11,680 --> 00:33:13,480
The battery's been disconnected, Boss.

275
00:33:20,280 --> 00:33:21,560
This one too.

276
00:33:46,600 --> 00:33:49,280
- Is it this one?
- No.

277
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:50,800
Not this.

278
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:07,600
Here.

279
00:34:18,400 --> 00:34:19,679
Checkmate!

280
00:34:20,520 --> 00:34:24,000
I'm sick, and you still
won't go easy on me?

281
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:26,639
If you're fighting,
you should give it your all.

282
00:34:27,239 --> 00:34:29,120
You taught me that, didn't you?

283
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:35,159
You sent Ya to interfere with me?

284
00:34:36,840 --> 00:34:38,000
Oh?

285
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:41,199
Pai, go outside first.

286
00:34:49,520 --> 00:34:51,600
Hey, Dad isn't well.

287
00:34:54,480 --> 00:34:55,880
That's none of your business.

288
00:34:56,480 --> 00:34:59,120
How is it not? He's not just your dad.

289
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:03,920
Prapai, please.

290
00:35:22,560 --> 00:35:26,520
You should be thanking Ya.
He saved your life.

291
00:35:27,240 --> 00:35:30,280
Do you even know who they're backed by?

292
00:35:30,880 --> 00:35:32,960
Stop acting hot-headed,

293
00:35:33,040 --> 00:35:35,160
or you'll destroy the entire gang.

294
00:35:36,400 --> 00:35:38,080
I don't care who they are.

295
00:35:39,760 --> 00:35:42,040
I'll make them bleed
for what they did to you.

296
00:35:43,280 --> 00:35:46,880
After what they did,
will you just let them walk free?

297
00:35:46,960 --> 00:35:48,920
Stay out of my business.

298
00:35:50,560 --> 00:35:52,120
Worried about your pride?

299
00:35:53,760 --> 00:35:55,320
And what about you?

300
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:58,920
You've been provoking others.
Don't think I don't know.

301
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:09,080
There you are.

302
00:36:10,960 --> 00:36:12,560
Wayu, stop!

303
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:16,080
I said stop!

304
00:36:18,880 --> 00:36:21,120
You love sticking your nose in, don't you?

305
00:36:22,760 --> 00:36:24,120
I said stop!

306
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,840
I know

307
00:36:32,920 --> 00:36:36,240
about you secretly selling
illegal guns on Leng's turf.

308
00:36:37,880 --> 00:36:41,720
Didn't I tell you not to do it?

309
00:36:44,160 --> 00:36:45,360
Why not?

310
00:36:52,200 --> 00:36:54,240
Do you know how much money it makes?

311
00:36:56,080 --> 00:36:57,520
You want a cut?

312
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:01,760
Just say how much. Say it!

313
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:09,000
If I say no, then it means no.

314
00:37:11,320 --> 00:37:15,160
If I catch you disobeying me again,

315
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:20,080
I'll send you to run the gambling den
on the island.

316
00:37:20,160 --> 00:37:21,680
And you won't come back.

317
00:37:24,240 --> 00:37:27,160
You've never cared about me.

318
00:37:29,160 --> 00:37:30,880
You've never seen my worth.

319
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:35,680
You think that lackey
is better than your own son?

320
00:37:36,480 --> 00:37:37,480
Huh?

321
00:37:39,280 --> 00:37:40,280
Just wait.

322
00:37:41,400 --> 00:37:44,880
One day, I'll be bigger than you!

323
00:37:47,120 --> 00:37:48,240
Just wait.

324
00:37:52,000 --> 00:37:53,360
Wayu!

325
00:38:07,680 --> 00:38:08,720
No.

326
00:38:10,880 --> 00:38:12,160
Let him go.

327
00:38:20,040 --> 00:38:23,600
I have to go to work soon.
I'm not free like some people.

328
00:38:23,680 --> 00:38:26,440
Alright, Miss Outstanding Journalist.

329
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:28,480
But don't overwork yourself.

330
00:38:29,320 --> 00:38:33,360
And don't forget
your future husband is waiting.

331
00:38:34,400 --> 00:38:35,240
Ew.

332
00:38:35,320 --> 00:38:37,800
Oh? Are you pregnant already?

333
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:42,200
Perfect then. Get married
and have the baby right away.

334
00:38:43,320 --> 00:38:45,520
Are you crazy? Stop imagining things.

335
00:38:48,200 --> 00:38:50,600
Alright, I've got to go to work now.

336
00:38:51,760 --> 00:38:53,480
See you tomorrow.

337
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:55,280
Bye.

338
00:39:54,320 --> 00:39:56,280
I HOPE YOU LIKE IT

339
00:39:56,360 --> 00:39:58,440
DO YOU EVEN SLEEP?
YOU KEEP UPLOADING THESE VIDEOS

340
00:39:58,520 --> 00:40:00,680
HIGH QUALITY AS ALWAYS

341
00:40:00,760 --> 00:40:03,680
NICE TITS, BUT HER ASS ISN'T THAT GOOD

342
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:08,280
I'VE MET HER BEFORE. SHE'S VERY ARROGANT
BUT NOT AT ALL IN BED

343
00:40:08,360 --> 00:40:14,480
WHO'S THE GUY? I'M JEALOUS
HE ALWAYS GETS THE GOOD ONES

344
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:20,200
MIGHT KILL THE MOOD IF YOU SAW HIS FACE

345
00:40:20,280 --> 00:40:25,640
I FEEL DEHYDRATED NOW

346
00:40:26,960 --> 00:40:31,600
I'M HUNGRY. ARE YOU READY TO SERVE?

347
00:40:35,840 --> 00:40:39,400
I CAN'T TAKE IT ANYMORE
LOOKS LIKE I'M GETTING SOME TONIGHT

348
00:40:40,640 --> 00:40:42,640
How is it? Good, right?

349
00:40:42,720 --> 00:40:45,840
ANYONE GOT RECOMMENDATIONS?
DROP THE LOCATION, PLEASE

350
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:53,720
Here.

351
00:40:56,960 --> 00:41:00,200
Don't take too long, and don't
let anyone know I helped you.

352
00:41:00,280 --> 00:41:01,440
Thank you so much.

353
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:03,200
Alright, I'll get back to work.

354
00:41:05,560 --> 00:41:06,960
- I'm going now.
- Kul.

355
00:41:08,280 --> 00:41:09,640
I think this is too risky.

356
00:41:09,720 --> 00:41:13,080
I need to find out
what really happened to Mai.

357
00:41:26,240 --> 00:41:27,440
Excuse me.

358
00:41:29,920 --> 00:41:31,760
Miss, please wait outside.

359
00:41:41,360 --> 00:41:43,760
Someone saw Mai at Heaven Club

360
00:41:43,840 --> 00:41:46,120
before she took several days off.

361
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:48,680
And when she came back,

362
00:41:49,480 --> 00:41:51,920
she wasn't happy at all,
like something had happened.

363
00:41:54,040 --> 00:41:57,080
They said she killed herself
because of work stress?

364
00:41:57,160 --> 00:41:59,640
No way. She loved being a news anchor.

365
00:42:03,760 --> 00:42:05,080
I don't believe it.

366
00:42:40,480 --> 00:42:41,920
This way, please.

367
00:42:54,000 --> 00:42:55,720
I already told you.

368
00:42:56,360 --> 00:42:57,880
I only drink with clients.

369
00:42:57,960 --> 00:43:00,640
Just drinking, nothing else.

370
00:43:00,720 --> 00:43:02,040
Is that so?

371
00:43:02,680 --> 00:43:04,840
Fine, then leave.

372
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:10,720
Then that video
will be released outside the group.

373
00:43:12,520 --> 00:43:13,800
Hey.

374
00:43:15,040 --> 00:43:16,920
You're really going to force me?

375
00:43:19,600 --> 00:43:21,480
I told you, I don't sell myself!

376
00:43:21,560 --> 00:43:23,320
Why risk ruining your reputation?

377
00:43:24,920 --> 00:43:29,240
Even other actresses
don't have a problem with it.

378
00:43:29,320 --> 00:43:31,800
So, actresses are supposed to be easy?

379
00:43:33,560 --> 00:43:37,120
I got here with my talent.
I didn't sleep my way up.

380
00:43:38,920 --> 00:43:40,480
Unlike parasites like you,

381
00:43:41,640 --> 00:43:43,520
living off women.

382
00:43:45,400 --> 00:43:46,720
Go find someone who's willing.

383
00:43:48,200 --> 00:43:50,560
Why force someone who doesn't want it?

384
00:43:50,640 --> 00:43:52,000
Why?

385
00:44:02,240 --> 00:44:03,840
Then why did you sleep with me before?

386
00:44:07,720 --> 00:44:11,440
You could've slept with any lowlife,
but instead…

387
00:44:23,640 --> 00:44:25,240
You're the same.

388
00:44:26,360 --> 00:44:29,720
You wanted someone with a good profile.

389
00:44:30,840 --> 00:44:33,000
You're no different from my clients.

390
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:36,720
They want you more than women
who sell themselves.

391
00:44:42,320 --> 00:44:46,000
Because they believe
you're of a higher class.

392
00:44:54,760 --> 00:44:56,120
You have a girlfriend,

393
00:44:57,280 --> 00:45:00,240
a sister, a mother.

394
00:45:02,080 --> 00:45:05,680
- How can you do this to me?
- But you're not them.

395
00:45:13,320 --> 00:45:14,920
If you don't want trouble,

396
00:45:16,480 --> 00:45:18,160
behave yourself.

397
00:45:20,120 --> 00:45:21,560
This is your warning.

398
00:45:23,880 --> 00:45:25,240
Let go.

399
00:45:59,240 --> 00:46:01,720
What were you doing
outside that VIP room for so long?

400
00:46:03,440 --> 00:46:06,040
There was a stain that wouldn't come off.

401
00:46:07,720 --> 00:46:09,840
That's why it took a while.

402
00:47:22,760 --> 00:47:26,080
Tonight, drinks are on me.
Order whatever you want.

403
00:47:27,800 --> 00:47:28,880
Thank you.

404
00:47:35,280 --> 00:47:38,840
Feel free to order anything.
It's my treat.

405
00:47:41,480 --> 00:47:42,600
No need.

406
00:47:43,720 --> 00:47:44,880
I can pay for my own drinks.

407
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:53,280
I caused you trouble.

408
00:47:56,600 --> 00:47:57,720
It's nothing, Boss.

409
00:47:58,320 --> 00:48:01,320
Don't forget, you gave me this life.

410
00:48:04,240 --> 00:48:07,480
Thank you for taking care of Wayu.

411
00:48:08,120 --> 00:48:10,000
I must not be a good father.

412
00:48:10,760 --> 00:48:13,440
That's why my son turned out like this.

413
00:48:17,840 --> 00:48:19,760
But you still have Ms. Prapai.

414
00:48:22,040 --> 00:48:23,040
Yes.

415
00:48:24,160 --> 00:48:26,800
She's nothing like her brother.

416
00:48:28,320 --> 00:48:30,280
My kids made me stop many things,

417
00:48:31,320 --> 00:48:34,560
human trafficking, drugs, guns,

418
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:37,520
because I started
thinking about my family.

419
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:44,120
When Mr. Wayu cools down,
he'll understand.

420
00:48:46,840 --> 00:48:49,960
Don't try to comfort me. Someone like him?

421
00:48:55,040 --> 00:48:58,600
And those who attacked you,
are we really letting them go?

422
00:48:59,600 --> 00:49:01,160
We'll wait for the right moment.

423
00:49:02,360 --> 00:49:05,200
At least they won't dare
make a move for now,

424
00:49:05,920 --> 00:49:07,440
knowing I'm still alive.

425
00:49:08,480 --> 00:49:12,520
But I'm more concerned about Wayu.

426
00:49:12,600 --> 00:49:14,600
He might cause even more trouble.

427
00:49:17,480 --> 00:49:18,680
Excuse me.

428
00:49:20,040 --> 00:49:23,040
You're Mr. Wayu, right?

429
00:49:30,160 --> 00:49:31,880
I'm not here to bother you,

430
00:49:32,880 --> 00:49:34,320
but I've heard about you.

431
00:49:35,760 --> 00:49:39,800
You took care of Leng completely.

432
00:49:44,480 --> 00:49:46,320
I truly respect you.

433
00:49:48,160 --> 00:49:49,960
He's been causing me trouble
for a long time.

434
00:49:51,640 --> 00:49:55,520
If you don't mind, may I buy you a drink?

435
00:49:56,040 --> 00:49:58,280
For a real hero.

436
00:50:01,120 --> 00:50:02,320
What do you want?

437
00:50:04,600 --> 00:50:06,600
Nothing in this world is free.

438
00:50:09,800 --> 00:50:14,240
You're sharp. That makes things easier.

439
00:50:16,360 --> 00:50:17,440
I…

440
00:50:19,600 --> 00:50:21,280
want to do business with you.

441
00:50:22,640 --> 00:50:26,480
I want to be your partner,
selling those black-market items.

442
00:50:33,240 --> 00:50:35,160
Why would I partner with you?

443
00:50:38,120 --> 00:50:38,960
You're right.

444
00:50:40,520 --> 00:50:41,480
I'm small.

445
00:50:42,600 --> 00:50:45,000
I can't run that kind of business alone.

446
00:50:49,160 --> 00:50:50,000
But…

447
00:50:50,920 --> 00:50:53,120
I do have connections.

448
00:50:54,560 --> 00:50:58,840
All those guys playing snooker…
hundreds of them.

449
00:51:03,040 --> 00:51:04,160
Boss.

450
00:51:06,160 --> 00:51:07,800
But the big boss said no.

451
00:51:21,880 --> 00:51:23,640
Where's that drink you said you'd buy?

452
00:51:24,960 --> 00:51:26,600
I wanna try it.

453
00:51:34,440 --> 00:51:35,840
At the snooker table?

454
00:51:36,560 --> 00:51:39,440
Yes. Someone came to talk business,

455
00:51:39,520 --> 00:51:41,440
praising him non-stop.

456
00:51:41,520 --> 00:51:44,720
He's in a good mood now.
He probably won't go looking for trouble.

457
00:51:45,320 --> 00:51:46,400
What kind of business?

458
00:51:48,160 --> 00:51:49,560
Whoever he's dealing with,

459
00:51:50,440 --> 00:51:52,880
wherever he's drinking, I don't care.

460
00:51:54,200 --> 00:51:56,600
As long as he's not picking up
a fight with those people.

461
00:51:57,960 --> 00:52:01,840
At least he still listens to me.

462
00:52:04,880 --> 00:52:07,560
Thanks. You can go rest.

463
00:52:09,240 --> 00:52:10,080
Yes, Boss.

464
00:52:11,960 --> 00:52:13,240
Call me if anything comes up.

465
00:52:46,640 --> 00:52:48,720
Can't you stay?

466
00:52:49,240 --> 00:52:51,560
My dad won't be home for a few days.

467
00:52:52,080 --> 00:52:55,760
Don't tempt me, or I might actually stay.

468
00:52:55,840 --> 00:52:56,720
Then stay.

469
00:53:03,360 --> 00:53:07,640
If Kul finds out I stayed over…

470
00:53:11,840 --> 00:53:13,280
She might think badly of you.

471
00:53:17,600 --> 00:53:19,680
But I'd never think badly of you.

472
00:53:20,520 --> 00:53:23,640
We love each other.
One day, she'll understand.

473
00:53:55,520 --> 00:53:56,560
Hey?

474
00:54:01,480 --> 00:54:03,520
Hey! What are you doing?

475
00:54:08,400 --> 00:54:09,440
Kul…

476
00:54:11,200 --> 00:54:13,320
We've searched everywhere.
There's nothing.

477
00:54:13,400 --> 00:54:15,040
It's not in the laptop either.

478
00:54:20,200 --> 00:54:21,600
Get up! Move!

479
00:54:22,360 --> 00:54:23,480
Now!

480
00:54:26,760 --> 00:54:27,600
No!

481
00:54:29,560 --> 00:54:31,160
Don't!

482
00:54:32,760 --> 00:54:34,760
- Kul!
- Come here!

483
00:54:38,480 --> 00:54:39,920
No.

484
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:02,720
You know what this is, right?

485
00:55:04,440 --> 00:55:05,440
Huh?

486
00:55:13,240 --> 00:55:15,200
Raka, run!

487
00:55:15,280 --> 00:55:16,160
Run!

488
00:55:20,920 --> 00:55:23,240
Mom.

489
00:55:23,320 --> 00:55:26,000
Mom! Mom!

490
00:55:27,200 --> 00:55:28,280
Mom!

491
00:55:29,160 --> 00:55:33,040
Mom! Let go of me!

492
00:55:34,600 --> 00:55:36,960
- Mom.
- Mom!

493
00:55:38,880 --> 00:55:40,320
Kul!

494
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:42,720
Kul!

495
00:55:43,560 --> 00:55:45,600
Kul!

496
00:55:46,280 --> 00:55:48,440
Kul!

497
00:55:50,640 --> 00:55:52,080
Mom!

498
00:55:55,320 --> 00:55:57,520
Vi. Vi.

499
00:55:58,440 --> 00:56:02,280
Are you home? Raka? Kul? Is anyone home?

500
00:56:05,120 --> 00:56:06,920
Hey! Go after him!

501
00:56:07,000 --> 00:56:08,760
Hey!

502
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,160
Stop!

503
00:56:10,240 --> 00:56:11,200
Raka.

504
00:56:11,280 --> 00:56:12,360
What happened?

505
00:56:20,360 --> 00:56:21,440
Enough.

506
00:56:25,520 --> 00:56:27,600
- Go after him.
- Yes.

507
00:58:03,040 --> 00:58:04,160
Did you find him?

508
00:58:04,240 --> 00:58:06,200
He's not down here.

509
00:58:06,280 --> 00:58:07,840
He's not up there either.

510
00:58:08,880 --> 00:58:10,240
Where the hell did he go?

511
00:59:07,960 --> 00:59:09,120
Mom…

512
00:59:12,440 --> 00:59:13,600
Mom…

513
00:59:16,360 --> 00:59:17,720
Kul…

514
01:00:03,360 --> 01:00:04,400
Let go!

515
01:00:15,080 --> 01:00:16,360
Twenty million? Fine.

516
01:00:16,440 --> 01:00:18,840
Then you'll only get her hand.

517
01:00:19,960 --> 01:00:21,880
- Uncle! Uncle!
- It hurts!

518
01:00:27,680 --> 01:00:30,040
<i>You're such a beautiful</i>
<i>and generous girlfriend.</i>

519
01:00:30,120 --> 01:00:32,200
Mr. Mahasamut is very lucky.

520
01:00:41,160 --> 01:00:44,280
I know I have to be careful.
I'll be there soon.

521
01:00:44,360 --> 01:00:46,720
The target is moving. You can proceed.

522
01:00:48,160 --> 01:00:49,840
Then who's going with her?

523
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:53,040
Pitbull is ready.

524
01:00:53,120 --> 01:00:55,080
- Which floor?
- You.

525
01:01:51,080 --> 01:01:53,440
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
